top_casts.text: Personal update -- second baby arrived last night. Mom, baby and big brother are all healthy and doing well. If I'm slow to respond, well... :)

If I could nudge Farcasters to do one thing: share stuff you're interested in *outside* of the main topics here -- crypto, web3, business, Farcaster. Don't worry about if it will "flop" from an engagement standpoint.

Helps make everyone a bit more multi-dimensional.

Obvious in retrospect mistakes for Farcaster so far:

1. Starting with desktop app vs. mobile (I love desktop like a child but mobile engagement and retention significantly better)

2. Focusing early onboarding to people with >10K Twitter followers. Virtually all churned.

Farcaster stats

November 2021: 300 MAU

November 17 2022: 2,000+ DAU

November 17 2023: ???

New feature on mobile

Direct Casts!

You can now send an end-to-end encrypted cast to anyone who follows you on Farcaster.

iOS only for now, coming soon to Android and desktop.
 https://i.imgur.com/SRGkDwA.jpg

Companies / software that inspire my product thinking:

- Apple
- Linear
- Vercel
- Gas
- Signal
- Cash App

For the record: despite the noise, Twitter will be fine.

Farcaster will succeed if it accomplishes 3 things:

1. Grow / retain quality DAUs; too quickly or too much churn will severely harm the network

2. Earn developer trust so they build apps for the long term

3. Network is sufficiently decentralized
